plan for integrating design and leadership, translating processes, principles, and practices from years of experience into tools of change for professional leaders. Quayle describes the key concepts of designed leadership, such as “make values explicit” and “learn from natural systems,” showing how strategic design can spur individual creativity and harness collective energy. For managers at any level, Designed Leadership uses original visuals and field-tested examples to teach the kind of thinking, theorizing, and practicing that result in long-lasting high performance in the workplace and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aLeadership. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311054330808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2017z9783110547740oZDB-23-DBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/quay1731240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231544689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231544689/original  a978-3-11-054330-8  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBVb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017